{"id":"math210-antideriv210-002","cid":"MATH 210","topic":"Integrals","subtopic":"Power rule for antiderivatives","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"Integrate: integral of {a}x^{n} dx. What is the coefficient of x^{new_exp210} in the result?","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":8},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":5}},"answer_expr":"antideriv210","steps":["Apply the power rule: int x^n dx = x^(n+1)/(n+1).","int {a}x^{n} dx = {a}/{n+1} * x^{new_exp210} + C.","Coefficient = {answer_antideriv210}."],"tags":["calculus","integration","power-rule"]}
